Text: Mr. Thummel projected that oil prices in the United States will settle at between $60 and $70 a barrel, which would lead to a roughly 25 cent increase in the retail price of gasoline.
Cause: Mr. Thummel projected that oil prices in the United States will settle at between $60 and $70 a barrel
Effect: a roughly 25 cent increase in the retail price of gasoline.
Sentence: <e1>Mr. Thummel projected that oil prices in the United States will settle at between $60 and $70 a barrel</e1>, which would lead to <e2>a roughly 25 cent increase in the retail price of gasoline.</e2>
